Special Weather Statement
National Weather Service Gray ME
222 PM EDT SAT JUL 1 2017

MEC005-011845-
Cumberland ME-
222 PM EDT SAT JUL 1 2017

...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Cumberland County
through 245 PM EDT...

At 222 PM EDT, a waterspout was reported over Lake Sebago or 7 miles
southwest of Raymond, nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Waterspout.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Waterspouts can easily overturn boats and create locally
         hazardous waters.

Locations impacted include...
Sebago Lake, Frye Island, Raymond Neck and Casco.

PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...

If on or near Sebago Lake, get away from the water and move to safe
shelter immediately. If you can hear thunder, you are close enough
to be struck by lightning. Move into dock and seek safe shelter now!
Do not be caught on the water in a thunderstorm.

